Assumption:
Assumption 1: $R$ is the quotient ring $\mathbb{C}[x,y,z]/(xy - (1 - z^2))$,
Assumption 2: $S$ is the quotient ring $\mathbb{C}[x,y,z]/(x^2y - (1 - z^2))$.
Assumption 3: $$\require{AMScd}
\begin{CD}
X \times_V Y @>>> Y\\
@VVV @VVV\\
X @>>> V
\end{CD}
$$
Problem: 
Prove that $R \not\cong S$ but $R[t] \cong S[t]$.
